The paper discusses a framework for modeling and recovering structures from cryo-electron microscopy data, which involves image processing, machine learning, and computational modeling. The paper's focus on modeling and recovering structures from noisy and heterogeneous data suggests that it could be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Bayesian formulation and Markov chain Monte Carlo algorithms suggests that it could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper's emphasis on modeling and analyzing complex systems suggests that it could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SI).
